Text: "ASTONISHING JOURNEY \n                    TO DEHRADUN\u2026.. \n          \
  \            HAVE A LOOK\u2026\u2026\nIf you want to lost yourself in majestic views\
  \ then DEHRADUN is a right place to visit. Dehradun is perfect place to spend holidays\
  \ in all prospective. The atmosphere of this place so pleasant and have lots of\
  \ \nmarvelous sight-viewing places.\n\nIn suburbs of Dehradun, \u2018Robber\u2019\
  s Cave\u2019 is situated which is also popularly known as \u2018Guchu Pani\u2019\
  . This place is surrounded by majestic hills and offers a glorious view of mountains.\
  \ Another wonderful place \nis \u2018Sahastradhara\u2019 meaning \u2018Thousands\
  \ of fold spring\u2019 which also well known for its therapeutic values as it has\
  \ \u2018Gandhak ka Pani\u2019 (sulphur water).\n\nDehradun also has \u2018Zoological\
  \ Garden\u2019 in the way to Mussorie which is known as Malsi Deer Park and it also\
  \ home of two horned Deer, Tiger, Neelgai, Peacock, crocodiles and other animals.\
  \ This is well maintained zoological garden to visit.\n\n\u2018Tapkeshwar Temple\u2019\
  \ is a famous cave Temple on the banks of a rivulet. \nThe water further flows in\
  \ to the cave to drip on to the \u2018Shiv Linga\u2019 inside. Sulphur Springs present\
  \ around temple makes for a therapeutic bath. It is also said that long ago instead\
  \ of water milk use to flow in to \ncave to drip down.\n\nThe \u2018Zonal Museum\u2019\
  \ is also well known for its collection of artifacts relating to origin, development\
  \ and sustenance of mankind on the earth, and stands witness to the ancient living\
  \ conditions and customs \nof its people. \u2018Forest Research Institute\u2019\
  \ also situated in Dehradun and it is spread over 4.5 sq km has imposing Colonial\
  \ and Greco-Roman Styles of Architecture.\n\u2018Tapovan Ashram\u2019 is located\
  \ along the Dehradun-Rajpur Road which surrounded by lush greenery and calm meadows,\
  \ Tapovan is delight to sense, to visit any time of the year. The Ashram also holds\
  \ periodic yoga courses for visitors to attend. It is placed along the banks of\
  \ \u2018River \nGanga\u2019.\n\nPaltan Bazar in Dehradun is great option for shopping.\
  \ As our trips are always incomplete without shopping, so don\u2019t forget to visit\
  \ Paltan Bazar which ideal place for shopping in Dehradun.\nThe Clock Tower is situated\
  \ in market of Dehradun has nearby good food centers\u2019. You can try Falooda,\
  \ Gulab Jamun, Bun Tickee etc\u2026\n        VISIT DEHRADUN AND IMMERSE \n     \
  \      YOURSELF IN ASTOUNDING \n                            VIEWS OF IT\u2026"
